          PROGRAM TO DEMONSTRATE INHERITANCE, 
                       DYNAMIC DISPATCH CONCEPTS
19 Feb 2026


AIM:    
To demonstrate interfaces, inheritance, polymorphism (static & dynamic), and use of super keyword in Java. 

ALGORITHM:
	Step 1: Start the program.
Step 2: Create a parent class with a method.
Step 3: Create a child class that extends the parent class.
Step 4: Override the parent method in the child class.
Step 5: Create a parent class reference and assign child object.
Step 6: Call the method using parent reference.
Step 7: Observe child method execution (dynamic dispatch).
Step 8: Stop the program.	

